  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The efficiency of epidural steroid injection in patients who has postherpetic neuralgia is
      well known. In this study, the purpose is whether the continous epidural steroid injection is
      effective or not.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Continous epidural injection will be done during 10 days. D group will be injected a 0.19%
      ropivacaine 8mL and dexametasone 1mg every other day during 10 days.

      Continous epidural injection will be done during 10 days N group will be injected a 0.19%
      ropivacaine 8mL only every other day during 10 days
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
